Part -1

Basic
: docker version
: docker -v
: docker info
: docker --help
: docker login
————————————
Images
: docker images
: docker pull
: docker rmi  :remove images
————————————
Containers
: docker ps :::shows all running containers
  docker ps -a::: show all the hidden containers
: docker run <container name or id> :::runs container with container id and tags like 'it'
  docker run --<Name of container> -it <UBUNTU> ::: (when image is not there, pull directly and run)
: docker start 
: docker stop
  docker attach <container name or id>:::Go inside of container
  docker kill <container name or id>::: Kills the running container
 docker rm <container name or id>::: deletes the running container
————————————
System
: docker stats
: docker system df disc memory
: docker system prune deltes all images with '-a' deletes all containes and files whoch are not used.
